{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "meta": {
    "name": "VR-7 Reference Sub",
    "author": "Matt Woolly",
    "category": "SubBass",
    "description": "A hardware-accurate sub tuned to the documented A4 = 442 Hz reference (the original unit's VR-7 calibration value), not the 440 Hz engine default. A deep -1 Oct square sub under a low, closed IR3109-style filter, square-plus-saw blend, minimal resonance and a fast clean amp envelope. Hardware-faithful 16' register and Triangle LFO (no software-only extension). Mono.",
    "tags": [
      "sub",
      "bass",
      "hardware-accurate",
      "442",
      "reference",
      "mono"
    ],
    "inspired_by": "hardware-reference tuning idiom",
    "sound_ext": false
  },
